transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, this is Charles.

Speaker 2: Hey Charles, how you doing?

Speaker 1: Good, how about yourself?

Speaker 2: I'm doing good.

Speaker 1: Hey, I got a concern I need to try to figure something out here.

Speaker 2: For some reason I'm getting a charge and more medications sent to me without my knowledge.

Speaker 1: All I get is an email that my debit card has been tapped for the $68 a month or however long it is, I'm not sure.

Speaker 2: So I went to the website, it doesn't give you a clear way to unsubscribe, so what do I do?

Speaker 1: I just got this and I don't want it anymore.

Speaker 2: Am I stuck with it?

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: So I have Gerald Ben in Devers, Texas?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, so with your prescription when it gets written up, it does come with refills.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: If you don't necessarily need the refills every single month, we completely understand.

Speaker 2: Okay, we understand not everybody pops these things like M&Ms.

Speaker 1: With that most recent order that you have, what you can do is write, refer to sender on it, throw it back in the mailbox.

Speaker 2: Mailman will come by either tomorrow or Monday, take it and send it right back to us for a refund.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And then that will be that.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Just shot out of the blue here, question.

Speaker 1: How are you doing on the first couple of orders?

Speaker 2: It's okay.

Speaker 1: I mean, it's okay.

Speaker 2: It's just I was going to just try it for however long, but I got the last one.

Speaker 1: I thought, well, let me try to cancel it.

Speaker 2: So I canceled my Google Wallet and then I got another one today.

Speaker 1: So I just want to, you know, it's just something I want to discontinue.

Speaker 2: Now, I didn't know what it was, so I have the bag open, but I haven't opened the bottle.

Speaker 1: Can I just put it back in the bag and tape it?

Speaker 2: Yeah, tape it up really, really good, write return to sender on it with a marker,

Speaker 1: and you should be good to go as far as them sending it back for free.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And then how long can I expect to get my refund?

Speaker 2: As soon as I'm already writing the notes, as soon as we have it back at our pharmacy,

Speaker 1: they're going to do a refund immediately.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Now, can I get that e-mail confirmation?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'll send one out.

Speaker 1: Expect that in about 30 to 40 minutes, okay?

Speaker 2: Our e-mail team should be busy.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: That'll work.

Speaker 1: And what's your name, sir?

Speaker 2: Charles.

Speaker 1: Charles, you've been a big help, Charles.

Speaker 2: I'll do this right away.

Speaker 1: Sounds good.

Speaker 2: All right, Gerald.

Speaker 1: Hope you have a great rest of your day.

Speaker 2: You too, sir.

Speaker 1: All right, take care.
